Responsibilities 
You will get the opportunity of working in a fast-paced environment developing algorithms and techniques leveraging text, speech, images, and video for analyzing content from users of Designer, Coach, and Live to build solutions that have the potential to transform peopleâ€™s lives. From fast evolving new intelligence features to long-range strategic investments, you will get the chance to ship world-class software to our enormous customer base. You will be surrounded by extremely talented and helpful colleagues and a great management team with lots of experience to learn from who are all deeply invested in helping you move your career forward. 
With services and our web platform, the teamenjoys the benefits of rich telemetry, data driven decisions, rapidly shipping at a daily cadence and building on top of the Azure platform. Our products and portfolio are rapidly expanding, and we are excited to meet the challenges of scale, performance, efficiency, and reliability as we build the world's best storytelling software. 
Qualifications 
MS/ Ph.D. in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering or related disciplines. 
2+ years' of experience with relevant projects in Natural Language Processing, Computational Linguistics, Speech Recognition, or Computer Vision. 
Fluency in C++/C# and Python preferred. 
Experience with statistical modeling and deep learning especially with frameworks such as PyTorch, Tensorflow or Keras. 
Effective communication skills and ability to work cross-group and across disciplines. 
Excellent skills in design, debugging and problem solving. 
Passion for customers, innovation, product quality, service excellence and test engineering. 
Experience in shipping high-quality products or services at-scale is a plus. 
